### List {#a99e0c545ced231517cfa301549fe8218}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::priority&#95;queue&lt;DGNode &#42;, std::vector&lt;DGNode &#42;&gt;, PriorityCmp&gt; llvm::sandboxir::ReadyListContainer::List</>}>
Control/Other dependencies are not modeled by the DAG to save memory.

These have to be modeled in the ready list for correctness. This means that the list will hold back nodes that need to meet such unmodeled dependencies.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/vectorize/include/llvm/transforms/vectorize/sandboxvectorizer/scheduler-h/#l00045">45</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/vectorize/include/llvm/transforms/vectorize/sandboxvectorizer/scheduler-h">Scheduler.h</a>.
